The paper presents a new data structure for GPUs that supports priority queue operations and bulk updates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions that the data structure is cache-efficient, which could place it in the Architecture (cs.AR) or Performance (cs.PF) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions that it out-performs existing algorithms on the GPU, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
